5:
Ahahaha! So you need to scrounge
up some materials, huh? Sounds like
a job for a pirate, if I've ever heard
one!
9:
This will be our first mission in quite
a while.
12:
I'm sure I can handle it, even with
one eye.
16:
Hey, Alk? Stella?
I haven't had the chance to tell you
yet, but...
19:
I decided to disband the Crimson
Blades.
32:
Well, it's just that Amelia and the
Mermaid Pirates are off to such an
amazing start. They even have
Colonel Selene on their side.
35:
They don't need someone like me to
lead them anymore. Besides, I have
a whole new crew to stand
shoulder-to-shoulder with now.
39:
And since we're equals, it doesn't
feel right to call myself captain
anymore.
44:
But... is this really what you want,
Marina?
48:
It is. These people here, they're my
new treasure.
53: That's right! She's one of us, now.
59: C'mon, Marina! It's time to go!
64:
Aye aye!
We'll be on our way, then!
72:
I will! I promise.
Have some of your special curry
ready for me when I get back, okay?
77:
Draco Voluntas, now departing!
Schult, Rooma, Rustamov! Look alive,
now!
89:
...Saying goodbye never gets easier,
does it?
94:
...You're joining the Abyss Exploration
Team, too?
99:
Looks like it. They're sendin' me out
on the next mission since they need
members who can handle a good
scrap.
102:
Claw and the others asked me to
come back to Fang Canyon. But
they've been fine without old
Whitetail this whole timethey sure
as hell don't need me now. 'Sides...
105:
You and Nao both have the same
habit of gettin' into trouble.
Someone's gotta look after her.
109:
...You really are a softie, Nimbus.
Always looking out for us.
113:
Only 'cause none of you look out for
your damn selves.
117:
...Thanks, Nimbus. For everything. I
can rest easy knowing Nao's with
you. Take care of her for me.
122:
Now that I've fulfilled my promise to
you, Alk... I, too, plan to leave
Starview Village.
126:
I wish to help Princess Lilith and the
others with their migration plans. To
do my utmost for the world that
made me who I am today.
129:
And... to repay them for allowing me
to regain my human form, even if
only for a short while.
134: I understand... It's your duty, after all.
148:
W-well... Not forever! We will surely
meet again before long
160:
Nephtim will fight to put a stop to
goodbyes! Everyone will remain
together!
165:
No, Nephtim! This ceremony of
graduation is not merely about
saying farewell, it is
172:
Graduation makes Nephtim's
loneliness levels rise...
180:
It's normal to feel lonely at a time
like this.
182:
But Inaho is right. Graduation isn't
just about saying goodbye.
186: I promise. I'll prove it to you myself.
194:
Alk, the interviews. I need your help
putting together information from
everyone.
203:
Ah... You mean the thing you
interviewed me and Challua for? To
record all of our adventures in a
book
213:
I see, now... I believe it is called a
"yearbook," yes?
An excellent idea! Leave the
bookbinding to me!
218:
A treasure, for Nephtim. So she
doesn't have to feel so alone.
